{"parse":{"title":"A Theory of Legal Order","pageid":35337248,"revid":854918483,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><i><b>A Theory of Legal Order</b></i> (<i><b>Teoria dell'Ordinamento Giuridico</b></i>) is a book of the Italian <a href=\"/wiki/Jurist\" title=\"Jurist\">jurist</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Norberto_Bobbio\" title=\"Norberto Bobbio\">Norberto Bobbio</a> about one of the <a href=\"/wiki/Ontology\" title=\"Ontology\">ontological</a> elements of <i><a href=\"/wiki/Philosophy_of_law\" title=\"Philosophy of law\">foundations of law</a></i> &#8212; the <i>juridical order</i>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Importance\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Importance</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Chapters[3]\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Chapters<sup>&#91;3&#93;</sup></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Criticism\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Criticism</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Bibliography\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Bibliography</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Importance\">Importance</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=A_Theory_of_Legal_Order&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Importance\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Seen by scholars as an important work<sup id=\"cite_ref-UNIN_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-UNIN-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-FILIPPI_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-FILIPPI-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> in understanding of a conceptual constructivist approach of the <a href=\"/wiki/Scientific_method\" title=\"Scientific method\">scientific way</a> of thinking law in the new era of the <a href=\"/wiki/Jurisprudence_of_values\" title=\"Jurisprudence of values\">jurisprudence of values</a>, Bobbio's book faces this challenge in five chapters.\n</p>\n<h2><span id=\"Chapters.5B3.5D\"></span><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Chapters[3]\">Chapters<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=A_Theory_of_Legal_Order&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Chapters[3]\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ol><li>Concept of law; going from the <i>juridical norm</i> to the <i>juridical order</i>.</li>\n<li>Unity of legal order;sources of law; the <i><a href=\"/wiki/Grundnorm\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Grundnorm\">grundnorm</a></i>; law and force.</li>\n<li>Cohesiveness of the legal order; solution of conflicts between norms.</li>\n<li>Completeness of legal order; the problem of <i>gaps of law</i>; <a href=\"/wiki/Analogy\" title=\"Analogy\">analogy</a>.</li>\n<li>Relationships between different legal orders, in different countries or in the same country in different times; different legal orders in the same State.</li></ol>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Criticism\">Criticism</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=A_Theory_of_Legal_Order&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Criticism\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>\"It's in the first chapter of the book, which could be a possible introduction, that the renowned jusphilosopher opted for not making. It is the connexion of this book, that study the complex of norms, with his former work, <a href=\"/wiki/A_Theory_of_Judicial_Norms\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"A Theory of Judicial Norms\">A Theory of Judicial Norms</a>, that analyzed isolatedly the norm; and then both constitute his integer general theory of law.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-SHV_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-SHV-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>\"<i>A Theory of Legal Order</i> is an attempt to solve some problems that the theory of the norm hadn't managed to solve or even had answer unsatisfatorily, as, for instance, the questions of the completeness and conflicts between norms. Bobbio declares expressly that his work can be considered a continuation or complement of <a href=\"/wiki/Kelsen\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Kelsen\">Kelsen</a>'s work, specially his <i>General Theory of Law and State</i>.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-JUS_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-JUS-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>\"In this work, the italian thinker analyzes no more the norm isolatedly, but the relationship between them inside an order. The author emphasizes the formal aspects of the unity, the cohesiveness and completess of law as a <i>closed</i> logical system, with the clear intention to survey the law with the objective criteria, <i><a href=\"/wiki/Sine_qua_non\" title=\"Sine qua non\">sine qua non</a></i> to rise them to a scientific level, through the juridical speech.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-UNIN_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-UNIN-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Bibliography\">Bibliography</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=A_Theory_of_Legal_Order&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Bibliography\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>Bobbio, Norberto.Teoria dell'ordinamento Giuridico. Torino:G. Giapichelli, 1960, <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/8834801857\" title=\"Special:BookSources/8834801857\">8834801857</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=A_Theory_of_Legal_Order&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Jurisprudence_of_values\" title=\"Jurisprudence of values\">jurisprudence of values</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Natural_law\" title=\"Natural law\">natural law</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Juridical_system\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Juridical system\">juridical system</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Rule_of_law\" title=\"Rule of law\">rule of law</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=A_Theory_of_Legal_Order&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-UNIN-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-UNIN_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-UNIN_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-te